Written and directed by Palme D'Or nominee Klaus Huttmann, THE LIST is a universal and
psychological thriller at the edge of our time. Christopher Cowin is in his mid 30s, a
family man who owns a small advertising agency. A court case he had recently lost has shown
him the rich and powerful always win! That is why Christopher creates the website THE LIST
On this site, users can label corrupt individuals in public life and award them points as to
how much of a menace they are. The result is a list of politicians, CEOs and bankers
The website quickly becomes a worldwide success but suddenly, whoever is number one on THE
LIST appears murdered and public opinion starts to turn against Christopher
